Hundreds of people were displaced after floods hit parts of Cape Town this week. Victims now want help from officials. eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Mother City is getting a reprieve from heavy rain this weekend, with only light showers forecast. But that's cold comfort for the many people in informal settlements who are homeless after flooding earlier this week. READ: Less rain, low temperatures expected in the Western Cape: SAWS They say there's been a lack of assistance from the disaster management centre and the housing department, so they’re seeking refuge at the Chris Hani community hall. The SA Weather Service says while no heavy rain is expected over the weekend, another cold front will hit the city midweek. * eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports.